detaileddescription.para: Base theme applied no matter what API

The collectionViewScrollBars style will be used as the default style for ItemsViewRenderer (the base renderer for CollectionView and CarouselView. We have to use a style to set up the scrollbars because there is currently no way to add them via code. When the renderer is created, we wrap its Context's theme with collectionViewTheme; that way, the collectionViewScrollBars style will be defined. With the style defined (and with the collectionViewStyle attribute defined in attrs.xml), we can apply the collectionViewScrollBars style explicitly to the renderer we are creating (and avoid forcing every child control to have scrollbars).
